<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How much does commercial dryer repair cost?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Our commercial diagnostic fee is $120, applied toward the repair once you approve the work. Most commercial dryer repairs run between $150 and $450. Heating element, thermal fuse, thermostat, drive belt, or door switch is toward the lower end. Motor or drum bearing replacement runs higher. Vent cleaning service runs $120–$200 depending on duct length and access. We provide a full written estimate before any work begins."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Which areas of Southern California do you cover for commercial dryer repair?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Same-day across Los Angeles, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, and Riverside counties, Koreatown, Hollywood, and Long Beach LA-side laundromats and apartment buildings; Anaheim, Garden Grove, and Costa Mesa OC laundromats; Thousand Oaks and Oxnard Ventura; Rancho Cucamonga, Riverside, and Ontario IE laundromats and multi-unit residential. Eight service territories total. Speed Queen, Huebsch, Dexter, Maytag Commercial, across the entire footprint. BHGS #A49573."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "My commercial dryer is taking too long to dry, what should I check first?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Check the lint screen and the exhaust vent before calling for service. Approximately 80% of 'dryer not heating properly' calls we receive in commercial laundry rooms are actually vent restriction issues, not heating element failures. A clogged lint screen or blocked exhaust vent causes the dryer to overheat, trip its thermal protection, and reduce heat output or shut down entirely. Clean the lint screen, check that the exterior vent cap opens freely, and if the issue persists, call us. If you can see or feel that the vent is significantly blocked, vent cleaning before or alongside the repair is necessary."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is a commercial dryer a fire risk if the vent is clogged?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes, this is a real and documented risk, not a scare tactic. According to NFPA data, dryers cause approximately 15,000 home structure fires per year in the US, with failure to clean dryer vents being the leading contributing factor. In commercial settings with high cycle volume, lint accumulates faster. A commercial dryer vent in a laundromat or apartment building running 20+ cycles per day can accumulate enough lint to pose a fire risk within months if not cleaned. If your dryer is running hot, taking longer than normal, or showing a burning smell, stop using it and call us for an inspection."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do you offer commercial dryer vent cleaning?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. We offer dryer vent cleaning as both a standalone service and as part of our commercial dryer repair visits. For laundromats and apartment buildings with multiple dryers, we can clean all vents on the same visit. Vent cleaning service runs $120–$200 depending on duct length and access. We use commercial rotary brush equipment to clear compacted lint that basic vacuuming can't reach. Vent cleaning every 6–12 months is the standard interval for commercial dryers in high-use environments."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do you repair Speed Queen, Huebsch, and Dexter commercial dryers?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. Speed Queen, Huebsch, and Dexter are the most common commercial dryer brands in SoCal laundromats and apartment buildings, across all five counties. We carry Speed Queen and Huebsch parts specifically. For Continental Girbau, UniMac, Maytag Commercial, and Milnor, we source parts through same-day commercial laundry distributors."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How often should commercial dryer vents be cleaned?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Every 6 months for laundromat dryers running 15+ cycles per day. Annually for apartment building dryers in moderate use. More frequently if duct runs are long or have multiple bends, SoCal apartment buildings (LA, Long Beach high-rises, OC condos, IE multi-unit residential) often have complex vent paths through walls and ceilings that accumulate lint faster than straight runs. We document vent condition and recommend intervals based on your specific installation."
      }
    }
  ]
})} />

<style>
