<!-- INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="intro-grid">
      <div class="intro-body">
        <p class="section-number">01, About This Service</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">Most commercial dryer failures are vent problems first. The ones that aren't are a fire risk if ignored.</h2>

        <p>Here's a fact that surprises most commercial laundry operators: approximately 80% of the "dryer not heating" calls we receive in commercial laundry rooms are actually vent restriction issues, not heating element or component failures. A clogged exhaust vent causes the dryer to overheat, trip its thermal protection, and shut down heat output. The symptoms look identical to a heating element failure but the fix is a vent cleaning, not a parts replacement. We check the vent before diagnosing components every time.</p>

        <p>The reason we're direct about this is the flip side: the 20% of cases that are actual component failures combined with a clogged vent are a genuine fire risk. According to NFPA data, dryers cause approximately 15,000 home structure fires per year in the US, with lint buildup and failure to clean vents being the leading contributing factor. In commercial settings running 15–20 cycles per day, lint accumulates faster and the risk compounds. A burning smell or dryer running unusually hot is not something to work around.</p>

        <p>We offer both services: mechanical repair for component failures, and commercial dryer vent cleaning as a standalone service. Same-day across LA, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, and Riverside counties, eight service territories total. Speed Queen and Huebsch parts are carried on service vehicles. For Dexter, Continental Girbau, UniMac, and Maytag Commercial, we source parts same-day through commercial laundry distributors. BHGS #A49573.</p>

        <div class="alert-fire">
          <div class="af-label">🔥 Burning Smell or Excessive Heat? Stop the Dryer Now.</div>
          <p>A burning smell from a commercial dryer is a fire safety signal, not something to complete a cycle through. Turn off the dryer immediately. Check the lint screen and vent for blockage. If the vent appears clear and the smell persists, call <strong>{phone}</strong> for emergency service. Do not restart the dryer until the cause is identified.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <aside class="sticky-cta">
        <div class="cta-label">Repair &amp; Vent Cleaning</div>
        <a href={phoneHref} class="cta-phone">{phone}</a>
        <a href={phoneHref} class="btn-cta">Call Now, Same Day</a>
        <a href="/book" class="btn-cta" style="background:#222; margin-top:-4px;">Schedule Online</a>
        <div class="cta-sub">Mon–Sun 7am–9pm · Commercial calls prioritized</div>
        <hr class="cta-divider" />
        <ul class="cta-detail">
          <li>Commercial diagnostic: $120</li>
          <li>Vent cleaning: $120–$200</li>
          <li>BHGS #A49573</li>
          <li>Speed Queen &amp; Huebsch parts</li>
          <li>5-county SoCal coverage</li>
          <li>Multi-dryer visits available</li>
        </ul>
