        <h3>Which areas of Southern California do you cover for commercial dryer repair?</h3>
        <p>Same-day across <strong>Los Angeles, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, and Riverside counties</strong>, Koreatown, Hollywood, and Long Beach LA-side laundromats and apartment buildings; Anaheim, Garden Grove, and Costa Mesa OC laundromats; Thousand Oaks and Oxnard Ventura; Rancho Cucamonga, Riverside, and Ontario IE laundromats and multi-unit residential. Eight service territories total. Speed Queen, Huebsch, Dexter, Maytag Commercial. BHGS #A49573.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>My commercial dryer is taking too long to dry, what should I check first?</h3>
        <p>Clean the lint screen completely, then check that the exterior vent cap opens freely with strong airflow when the dryer is running. About 80% of slow-drying calls are vent restriction, not heating failures. If the vent is clear and the problem persists, call us at {phone}.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Is a commercial dryer a fire risk if the vent is clogged?</h3>
        <p>Yes, documented by NFPA. Dryers cause approximately 15,000 structure fires annually in the US, with lint buildup and failure to clean vents as the leading factor. Commercial dryers running 15–20 cycles per day accumulate lint much faster than residential units. A burning smell means stop the dryer immediately and call us.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Do you offer commercial dryer vent cleaning?</h3>
        <p>Yes, as a standalone service and as part of repair visits across all five SoCal counties. We use commercial rotary brush equipment to clear compacted lint that basic vacuuming can't reach. $120–$200 per dryer depending on duct length and access. Multi-dryer building visits available.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Do you repair Speed Queen, Huebsch, and Dexter commercial dryers?</h3>
        <p>Yes. Speed Queen and Huebsch parts carried on the van. Dexter, Continental Girbau, UniMac, and Maytag Commercial sourced same-day through commercial laundry distributors.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>How often should commercial dryer vents be cleaned?</h3>
        <p>Every 6 months for laundromat dryers running 15+ cycles per day. Annually for apartment building dryers in moderate use. More frequently if duct runs are long with multiple bends, common in SoCal apartment installations across LA, Long Beach, OC condos, and IE multi-unit residential. We document vent condition and recommend intervals based on your specific setup.</p>
